h3cVoiceIf.name: h3cVoiceIf

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

h3cVoiceIf.contactinfo: PLAT Team Huawei 3Com Technologies co.,Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com Zip:100085
h3cVoiceIf.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of the voice interface general configuration.

h3cVoIfConfigTable.name: h3cVoIfConfigTable
h3cVoIfConfigTable.description: The table contains configurable parameters for both analog voice interface and digital voice interface.

h3cVoIfConfigEntry.name: h3cVoIfConfigEntry
h3cVoIfConfigEntry.description: The entry of voice interface table.

h3cVoIfCfgPortNumber.name: h3cVoIfCfgPortNumber
h3cVoIfCfgPortNumber.description: The port number of voice interface.

h3cVoIfCfgGroupNumber.name: h3cVoIfCfgGroupNumber
h3cVoIfCfgGroupNumber.description: The group number of voice interface. For an analog interface, the value is 255.

h3cVoIfCfgCngOn.name: h3cVoIfCfgCngOn
h3cVoIfCfgCngOn.description: This object indicates whether the silence gaps should be filled with background noise.

h3cVoIfConfigInputGain.name: h3cVoIfConfigInputGain
h3cVoIfConfigInputGain.description: This object indicates the amount of gain added to the receiver side of the voice interface. Unit is 0.1 db.

h3cVoIfConfigOutputGain.name: h3cVoIfConfigOutputGain
h3cVoIfConfigOutputGain.description: This object indicates the amount of gain added to the send side of the voice interface. Unit is 0.1 db.

h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch.name: h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch
h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch.description: This object indicates whether the echo cancellation is enabled.

h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancellDelay.name: h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancellDelay
h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancellDelay.description: This object indicates the delay of the echo cancellation for the voice interface. This value couldn't be modified unless h3cVoIfCfgEchoCancelSwitch is enable. Unit is milliseconds.

h3cVoIfCfgPlarNumber.name: h3cVoIfCfgPlarNumber
h3cVoIfCfgPlarNumber.description: This object indicates the E.164 phone number for plar mode.

h3cVoIfCfgDescription.name: h3cVoIfCfgDescription
h3cVoIfCfgDescription.description: This object indicates the description of voice interface

h3cVoIfCfgStatus.name: h3cVoIfCfgStatus
h3cVoIfCfgStatus.description: This object indicates the status of voice interface.

h3cVoIfCfgCallingNumSubstRule.name: h3cVoIfCfgCallingNumSubstRule
h3cVoIfCfgCallingNumSubstRule.description: This object indicates a calling number substitute rule.

h3cVoIfCfgCalledNumSubstRule.name: h3cVoIfCfgCalledNumSubstRule
h3cVoIfCfgCalledNumSubstRule.description: This object indicates a called number substitute rule.

h3cVoIfCfgSubLine.name: h3cVoIfCfgSubLine
h3cVoIfCfgSubLine.description: This object indicates the port subscriber line name.
